    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="480" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hirsch</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 25,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 134 of the 4th
                        instant, by which it appears that the statements made by Moses Angel and S.
                        Kanstoroom, the American citizens referred to in your No. 99, and those of
                        the local authorities at Jerusalem, in respect to their arrest last November
                        for alleged default in the payment of taxes, are quite at variance.</p>
                <p>The steps you have taken to ascertain the facts are approved.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
